CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 22, 1941, pg. 10, reads: "World Fellowship pageant presented by the World Fellowship Committee of Centre Avenue Branch YWCA last Friday. The pageant was directed by Mrs. Helen Dandridge.  Mrs. W. T. Poole is chairman of the committee. All nations were represented in native costume.  Participants were 'Y' committee heads and members."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women dressed in ethnic costumes, including Harriet Lewis holding fan sixth from left, posed in front of American flag, for world fellowship pageant in Centre Avenue YWCA
